The paper discusses the ability of variational autoencoders to generalize to unseen examples in domains with a large combinatorial space of feature values. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on evaluating the generalization of VAEs, machine learning (cs.LG) is the most likely sub-category.
